name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Respondent, v. Keith E. SNYDER, Petitioner

parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Respondent, v. Keith E. SNYDER, Petitioner.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 30th day of May, 1996, the Petition for Allowance of Appeal is GRANTED limited to the issue of whether petitioner was denied due process of law by the eleven year delay in his arrest. This case is to be orally argued.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

attorneys: John P. Moses, Charles P. Gelso, for petitioner.
casebody.head_matter:
677 A.2d 831
COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Respondent, v. Keith E. SNYDER, Petitioner.
Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
May 30, 1996.
John P. Moses, Charles P. Gelso, for petitioner.
